added.title: Books
added.description: Raven shows the rest of the Titans that books can be fun.

added.title: Starfire the Terrible
added.description: When Robin needs an archenemy, Starfire generously offers to fill the role and she exceeds expectations.

added.title: Lazy Sunday
added.description: When the Titans replace the couch with a treadmill, Cyborg and Beast Boy must get guidance from the couch spirit.

added.title: Power Moves
added.description: When Robin starts doing power moves with Cyborg, Beast Boy gets very jealous.

added.title: The Left Leg
added.description: When the gang bands together to form a giant robot, Robin is relegated to the left leg - but he makes the left leg count!

added.title: The Mustache
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's wish comes true when they suddenly turn into men.

added.title: The Date
added.description: Gumball discovers the difference between a "date" and a "pet's funeral"...the hard way.

added.title: The Club
added.description: When Gumball rejects "The Rejects Club", the rejects wreak their revenge.

added.title: The Wand
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make their dad believe in magic again.

added.title: The Ape
added.description: Ms Simian sets out to "befriend" Gumball in order to win a Favourite Teacher Award.

added.title: Power Punchers
added.description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

added.title: Creek Cart Racers
added.description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

added.title: Secret Book Club
added.description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

added.title: Jextra Perrestrial
added.description: JP believes he may be from another planet, so Craig tries to help him make contact.

added.title: The Takeout Mission
added.description: Kelsey leads her friends on the most important quest ever, picking up takeout for dinner.

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: A thunderstorm forces Chloe to spend the night at the Cave with the Bears. When Chloe's parents tell the Bears to protect Chloe, they take the task a bit too seriously.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Ghostfreaked Out
added.description: Ben's internal demons get externalized when Ghostfreak escapes from his watch and becomes a full fledged being on his own. The renegade alien then realizes he needs to meld with Ben's DNA in order to survive.

added.title: Ocean Gem
added.description: The Ocean disappears on the first day of summer and Beach City is in a panic.

added.title: House Guest
added.description: After injuring his leg, Greg comes to live with Steven and unintentionally interferes with Steven's powers.

added.title: Space Race
added.description: Steven attempts to build a spaceship to let Pearl revisit the wonders of the cosmos.

added.title: Secret Team
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Pearl accidentally pop a bubbled gem and form Secret Team to secretly retrieve the missing shards.

added.title: Island Adventure
added.description: Steven takes Lars and Sadie on a vacation to a magical beach to mend their friendship.

added.title: It Came From the Nightosphere
added.description: Against Marceline's wishes, Finn conjures her father, the Lord of Evil, and attempts to reconcile their rocky relationship. But when the Lord of Evil discovers his daughter has turned the family axe into a bass guitar, he takes it from her and starts sucking up all the souls in Ooo! Finn must find a way to stop the Lord of Evil and get Marceline's guitar back.

added.title: Loyalty to the King
added.description: There's a new "Nice King" in Ooo, and he looks kinda like someone else we know.

added.title: Blood Under the Skin
added.description: Finn goes on an embarrassing quest to get armor to fit in with some really cool knights.

added.title: Storytelling
added.description: When Jake becomes sick, the only thing that can cure him is a good story, so he asks Finn to go out and find one. The story must have excitement, romance, suspense and, of course, a happy ending. When nothing interesting happens, Finn tries to make the story happen, accidentally turning the forest animals against each other and him!

added.title: The Eyes
added.description: One night, an exhausted Finn and Jake are creeped out by an odd-looking horse that mysteriously appears outside the treehouse and keeps them awake. They try everything they can think of to get rid of the freaky horse, but nothing seems to work.

added.title: Stick Hockey
added.description: After Benson unjustifiably throws out Mordecai and Rigby's stick hockey table, he feels guilty and tries to help them get it back.

added.title: Bet to Be Blonde
added.description: Rigby wins a bet with Mordecai and makes him get a blonde perm.

added.title: Skips Strikes
added.description: Skips reveals himself to be an excellent bowler, until he realizes he has to bowl Death's team.

added.title: In the House
added.description: Rigby eggs the wrong house and gets cursed by a wizard.

added.title: Creepy Doll/Death Metal Crash Pit
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby discover an old Victorian Doll that Pop's has not played with or seen since he was a child and unwittingly unleash its pent up rage against him.  Muscle Man and High Five Ghost want to crash an old RV into a pit, but it's haunted by an 80s death metal band.

added.title: In the Garden of Good and Eddie
added.description: When the girls try a quick-fix on their neglected veggie garden, they are left with a giant, mooching tomato worm they must care for.

added.title: Road Trippin'
added.description: Realizing her and the Professor don't have much in common, Bubbles schedules a road trip with just the two of them.

added.title: The Big Sleep
added.description: When the Professor's latest invention wreaks havoc in the house, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop it before it escapes.

added.title: The Secret Life of Blossom Powerpuff
added.description: When Blossom can't join her favorite school club, she imagines what her life would be like if she joined other clubs.

added.title: Halt and Catch Silico
added.description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

added.title: Rough Riders Elementary
added.description: When a corporate sponsorship of Clarence's school turns into an ominous corporate takeover, Clarence must stand up to the the man, no matter how tasty the chicken may be.

added.title: Nothing Ventured
added.description: Clarence and Sumo look to throw together some quick cash so they can invest in Chad and Sumo's dad's new business venture, a boutique sculpture shop.

added.title: Bedside Manners
added.description: After a nasty spill lands Belson in a full body cast, Clarence pays his bedridden friend a visit at the hospital, but what Clarence thinks will cheer him up might actually drive Belson totally crazy!

added.title: Jeff Wins
added.description: Jeff enlists Clarence to help him prepare for the big Aberdale cook-off. Will Jeff keep his cool or freak out and toss his dish away like in years past?

added.title: Suspended
added.description: Clarence and Sumo hit the jackpot when they get suspended for a week, learning all sorts of different facts they'd never learn in class, but after a few days the suspension takes its toll, boredom sets in and the boys want to go back.

added.title: Prank Wars
added.description: When Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus engage in a prank war, Mr. Gus ends up pulling the biggest prank, only realizing too late that it will get Pizza Steve eaten.

added.title: 1992 Called
added.description: Uncle Grandpa travels back to the year 1492 to retrieve a pair of pants.

added.title: Bezt Frends
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to extreme measures to surpass Pizza Steve as Pizza Steve's best friend.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: Greed causes Pizza Steve's latest business venture to backfire.

added.title: Hide and Seek
added.description: A game of hide and seek uncovers a neglected remnant from Uncle Grandpa's past.

added.title: These Little Piggies Went to Market/Now Museum, Now You Don't
added.description: These Little Piggies Went to Market: Their first trip to a big grocery store fascinates the Baby Looney Tunes. After warning the others to stick to Granny's shopping list, Baby Bugs succumbs to buying a favorite treat then feels guilty./Now Museum, Now You Don't: Their very first trip to an art museum unleashes creative energy, turning the Baby Looney Tunes into enthused culture connoisseurs and budding artists. Baby Bugs recreates the museum experience back at Granny's house, finding abundant art history in everyday objects to the others' sheer delight.

added.title: Take Us Out to the Ballgame/Clues Encounters of the Tweety Kind
added.description: Take Us Out to the Ball Game: The Baby Looney Tunes experience their very first big stadium baseball game. Lola's favorite team's star batter gets her undivided attention until Lola's coaching affects the very outcome of the contest./Clues Encounters of the Tweety Kind: Tweety feels neglected when no one wants him on their museum scavenger hunt team. Using his innate sleuthing abilities and the help of a friendly museum guard, Tweety proves to be the best scavenger hunter of them all. Once Tweety wins the contest, everyone wants him on their team.

added.title: A Bully for Bugs/The Wheel Deal
added.description: A Bully for Bugs: With Floyd's adult assistance, Baby Bugs and the Baby Looney Tunes learn an effective way to deal with a bully. /The Wheel Deal: Everyone's excited about a grand bicycle outing through the park, everyone except Tweety whose little legs don't quite reach the pedals. Frustrated after riding on the back of Floyd's bicycle while everyone else has fun, Tweety is ready to go home.

added.title: Oh Brother, Warehouse Art Thou?/Flu the Coop
added.description: Oh, Brother, Warehouse Art Thou?: Baby Sylvester is overcome with angst because Granny's broken old chair, his favorite napping place, must be replaced by a new, unfamiliar piece of furniture. The other Baby Looney Tunes work together to help turn Sylvester's trepidation into enjoyment during their mammoth furniture-shopping adventure./Flu the Coop: Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy decide to team up and unlike the other Baby Looney Tunes, fake having received their annual flu shots at the local clinic. The joke's on them when they awaken on the day of Granny's big party unable to have fun because they both have the flu.

added.title: Blast Off Bugs/Baby Brouhaha
added.description: Blastoff Bugs: Baby Bugs tries to realize his dream of traveling to the moon while the Baby Looney Tunes are on a space museum visit./Baby Brouhaha: Overhearing Granny on the phone say she's expecting a baby, Baby Bugs goes into overdrive, revving up the Baby Looney Tunes to prepare to care for an infant.

added.title: Log Cabin Fever/A Mid-Autumn Night's Scream
added.description: Log Cabin Fever: Granny takes the Baby Looney Tunes back to a simpler lifestyle during a rustic weekend spent in an 1800's log cabin, where they learn to enjoy life minus all modern conveniences. Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy get in trouble for smuggling their palm-sized computer game along, and they face Granny's consequences./A Mid-Autumn Night's Scream: The Baby Looney Tunes first Halloween involves a costume contest for Lola, Melissa and Petunia, group trick-or-treating and Sylvester overcoming his fear of confronting an allegedly scary neighbor.

added.title: Are We There Yet/Save Our Cinnamon
added.description: Are We There, Yet?: During a long road trip, Floyd, obsessed with taking the Baby Looney Tunes to visit the distant, annual Acme Garlic Festival, endures countless variants of the universal kid question, are we there, yet? Despite Floyd's garlic agenda, fate has other plans./Save Our Cinnamon: Granny's sister's beloved bakery, Cakery Bakery Dock, home of her wonderful trademark cinnamon rolls, is being put out of business so her landlord can tear down the bakery to build a parking lot. This galvanizes the Baby Looney Tunes to work together to bake one giant cinnamon roll as a tourist attraction to save the bakery, a project that ends up involving the whole town.

added.title: Lights! Camera! Tweety!/Backstage Bugs
added.description: Lights, Camera, Tweety!: The Baby Looney Tunes are very eager to visit the local TV station, home of their favorite live children's show. When Floyd accidentally locks them inside the studio moments before airtime, they are forced to put on today's program all by themselves!/Backstage Bugs: Baby Bugs can't wait to see his favorite children's musical group, The Wormies, and he absolutely thrills to the notion of possibly meeting his personal hero, Willie Wormie, backstage after the show. But Bugs fails to heed Floyd's warning about staying with the group in the crowded arena and suffers consequences when he gets separated from Floyd.

added.title: Bend It Like Petunia/He'll Be Zoomin' Round the Mountain (song)/Cock-A-Doodle-Doo-It!
added.description: Bend It Like Petunia: The Baby Looney Tunes learn all about soccer from Floyd, who surprisingly is an enthused soccer expert. At first awkward, Baby Petunia works the hardest and displays the best sportsmanlike attitude, eventually becoming the very finest all-around soccer player of all the Baby Looney Tunes./Cock-A-Doodle Doo It!: On their first farm visit, the Baby Looney Tunes meet a young, dispirited rooster named Baby Foghorn Leghorn. They work together to build his self-confidence, unleashing powers of persuasion and elocution that even Foghorn never knew he had.

added.title: Wrong!/Win, Lose or Daffy
added.description: Wrong!: On an orchard outing, picking bushels of fresh apples for Granny's home-baked pies, the Baby Looney Tunes encounter Melissa, who is in a mood to tell everyone that her method of apple picking is the only way./Win, Lose or Daffy: A day playing miniature golf is fun for everyone but Baby Daffy, who believes he must beat everyone else at the game. At the end of the day, all but Daffy are having a good time regardless of how they scored.

added.title: A Turtle Named Mrytle/Oh My Darling Coyote (song)/There's Nothing Like a Good Book
added.description: A Turtle Named Myrtle: A trip to the seashore brings the Baby Looney Tunes into contact with a just-hatched turtle that Melissa, apart from the rest because of her bossy attitude, names Myrtle. Melissa just loves little Myrtle and wants to keep her from walking into the ocean so that she may take Myrtyle home for herself./There's Nothing Like a Good Book: A nagging question regarding the composition of the moon brings the Baby Looney Tunes to experience their very first visit to the library.

added.title: The Dolly Vanishes/Vive Le Pew, Le Skunk (song)/Duck's Reflucks
added.description: The Dolly Vanishes: On an overnight train trip to visit Floyd at college, Lola's doll vanishes. Baby Bugs acts as a detective as he tries to solve the missing Edna mystery via a series of simple flashbacks, seen from each Baby Looney Tunes' point of view./Duck's Reflucks: Baby Daffy has Baby Bugs right where he wants him, as the subject of his digital photography and at the mercy of his endless, egocentric creative whims.

added.title: Stop and Smell Up the Flowers/Firehouse Frolics
added.description: Stop and Smell Up the Flowers: The Baby Looney Tunes explore a world of botanic wonder as they search for just the right spot to plant a young lemon tree./Firehouse Frolics: The Baby Looney Tunes tour the local fire station, learning fire prevention tips from friendly Fireman Frank. Later, Baby Daffy, the most reluctant and uninterested participant, displays the most fire-fighting knowledge when he is suddenly tested by a real-life emergency at Granny's house.
